'''GW190521'''（或稱'''GW190521g'''，最初稱為'''S190521g'''）<ref name="PRL-20200902">{{cite journal |language=en |author=Abbott, R. |display-authors=et al. |title=GW190521: A Binary Black Hole Merger with a Total Mass of 150 M ⊙ |journal=[[Physical_Review_Letters|Physical Review Letters]] |date=2020-09-02 |volume=125 |issue=10 |pages=101102 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.125.101102 }}</ref>，是指兩個黑洞合併產生的一次[[重力波_(相對論)|引力波]]訊號。這次的黑洞合併被指與一道閃光有關係，若與黑洞合併有關，合併在第三個[[超大質量黑洞|超大質量黑洞]]附近。<ref name="NASA-20200625" /><ref name="NYT-20200625" />由[[雷射干涉引力波天文台|雷射干涉引力波天文台]]（{{lang|en|LIGO}}）和[[室女座干涉儀|室女座干涉儀]]探測器（{{lang|en|Virgo}}）於2019年5月21日[[協調世界時|協調世界時]]03:02:29觀測到<ref name="UL-2020">{{cite news |language=en |title=GW trigger S190521g ('GW 190521') |url=https://www.swift.ac.uk/LVC/S190521g/ |date=2020 |work=[[萊斯特大學|萊斯特大學]] |accessdate= |archive-date=2020-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200628111356/https://www.swift.ac.uk/LVC/S190521g/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，並在美國時間2020年9月2日正式發佈<ref name="AJ-20200902" /><ref name="PRL-20200902" /><ref name="LIGO-20200902" /><ref>{{cite news | language=zh-tw | url=https://www.cna.com.tw/news/firstnews/202009030128.aspx | title=最大規模雙黑洞合併 科技部清大參與發現過程 | publisher=中央通訊社 | date=2020-09-03 | access-date=2020-09-09 | archive-date=2020-09-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200905112020/https://www.cna.com.tw/news/firstnews/202009030128.aspx | dead-url=no }}</ref>；在離地球約170億光年外發生<ref name="PRL-20200902"/><ref name="NYT-20200903" />，在往[[后髮座|后髮座]]、[[獵犬座|獵犬座]]和[[鳳凰座|鳳凰座]]方向位於765[[平方度|平方度]]的範圍內發生<ref name="NASA-20190521">{{cite web |language=en |last=Mo |first=Geoffrey |title=GCN Circular - Number: 24640 - LIGO/Virgo S190521g: Updated sky localization |url=https://gcn.gsfc.nasa.gov/other/GW190521g.gcn3 |date=2019-05-21 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |accessdate=2020-09-09 |archive-date=2020-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200627180941/https://gcn.gsfc.nasa.gov/other/GW190521g.gcn3 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="LIGO-20190521">{{cite web |language=en |title=Superevent info - S190521g |url=https://gracedb.ligo.org/superevents/S190521g/view/ |date=2019-05-21 |work=LIGO |accessdate= |archive-date=2020-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200628043832/https://gracedb.ligo.org/superevents/S190521g/view/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NASA-20200625">{{cite news |language=en |last=Cofield |first=Calla |title=Black Hole Collision May Have Exploded With Light |url=https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=7688 |date=2020-06-25 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |accessdate= |archive-date=2020-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200628032649/https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=7688 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20200625">{{cite news |language=en |last=Overbye |first=Dennis |title=Two Black Holes Colliding Not Enough? Make It Three - Astronomers claim to have seen a flash from the merger of two black holes within the maelstrom of a third, far bigger one. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/25/science/black-hole-collision-ligo.html |date=2020-06-25 |work=The New York Times |accessdate= |archive-date=2020-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200625153002/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/25/science/black-hole-collision-ligo.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="PHYS-20200625">{{cite news |language=en |author=Gradute Center, CUNY |title=Black hole collision may have exploded with light |url=https://phys.org/news/2020-06-black-hole-collision.html |date=2020-06-25 |work=Phys.org |accessdate= |archive-date=2020-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626004744/https://phys.org/news/2020-06-black-hole-collision.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

GW190521經分析後，訊號分別由85個和66個[[太陽質量|太陽質量]]（<var>M</var><sub>☉</sub>）的黑洞合併發出<ref name="FRBS-20200903">{{cite news |last=Siegel |first=Ethan |title=LIGO's Biggest Mass Merger Ever Foretells A Black Hole Revolution |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/startswithabang/2020/09/03/ligos-biggest-mass-merger-ever-foretells-a-black-hole-revolution/ |date=2020-09-03 |work=[[Forbes|Forbes]] |accessdate= |archive-date=2020-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200904074001/https://www.forbes.com/sites/startswithabang/2020/09/03/ligos-biggest-mass-merger-ever-foretells-a-black-hole-revolution/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，合併產生142個太陽質量的黑洞，其餘9個太陽質量則轉化成重力波能量，為首次觀測到中介質量黑洞真實存在，亦錄得有史以來最大型的黑洞合併事件。<ref name="AJ-20200902">{{cite journal |language=en |author=Abbott, R. |display-authors=et al. |title=Properties and Astrophysical Implications of the 150 M ⊙ Binary Black Hole Merger GW190521 |journal=The Astrophysical Journal |date=2020-09-02 |volume=900 |issue=1 |pages=L13 |doi=10.3847/2041-8213/aba493 }}</ref><ref name="PRL-20200902" /><ref name="LIGO-20200902">{{cite news |language=en |author=Martin |title=GW190521: The Most Massive Black Hole collision Observed To Date |url=https://www.ligo.org/science/Publication-GW190521/flyer.pdf |date=2020-09-02 |work=LIGO Scientific Collaboration |accessdate= |archive-date=2020-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200904170948/https://www.ligo.org/science/Publication-GW190521/flyer.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | language=zh-hk | url=https://www.thestandnews.com/cosmos/ligo-%E8%88%87-virgo-%E7%A2%BA%E8%AA%8D%E8%BF%84%E4%BB%8A%E5%B7%B2%E7%9F%A5%E6%9C%80%E5%A4%A7%E5%9E%8B%E9%BB%91%E6%B4%9E%E5%90%88%E4%BD%B5-%E8%B3%AA%E9%87%8F%E7%82%BA%E5%A4%AA%E9%99%BD-142-%E5%80%8D/ | title=LIGO 與 Virgo 確認迄今已知最大型黑洞合併　質量為太陽 142 倍 | publisher=立場新聞 | date=2020-09-03 | access-date=2020-09-09 | archive-date=2020-09-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200911151544/https://www.thestandnews.com/cosmos/ligo-%E8%88%87-virgo-%E7%A2%BA%E8%AA%8D%E8%BF%84%E4%BB%8A%E5%B7%B2%E7%9F%A5%E6%9C%80%E5%A4%A7%E5%9E%8B%E9%BB%91%E6%B4%9E%E5%90%88%E4%BD%B5-%E8%B3%AA%E9%87%8F%E7%82%BA%E5%A4%AA%E9%99%BD-142-%E5%80%8D/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 對物理學的意義 ==
GW190521由於形成和組成的黑洞質量之大，被指是重大的發現。恆星演化理論認為恆星形成的黑洞最大只有約{{solar mass|60}}<ref name="Mapelli2020">{{cite journal|language=en | last1=Mapelli | first1=M. | last2=Spera | first2=M.| last3= Montanari | first3=E.| last4=Limongi | first4=M.| last5= Chieffi | first5=A.| last6= Giacobbo | first6=N. | last7=Bressan | first7=A. | last8=Bouffanais | first8=Y. | title=Impact of the Rotation and Compactness of Progenitors on the Mass of Black Holes | journal=The Astrophysical Journal |volume= 888|issue= 2|year= 2020|pages= 76|doi= 10.3847/1538-4357/ab584d}}</ref>，令此數值以上出現很大的黑洞質量間隙。GW190521所觀測到的{{solar mass|{{val|85|21|14}}}}和{{solar mass|{{val|142|28|16}}}}黑洞都在質量間隙中，證明了其可以以較小的黑洞合併形成。<ref name="AJ-20200902"/>

在此之前，只有間接證據證明100至10萬倍[[太陽質量|太陽質量]][[中介質量黑洞|中介質量黑洞]]的存在，亦不知道他們怎麼形成，<ref>{{cite journal |language=en | bibcode=2004IJMPD..13....1M | title=Intermediate-Mass Black Holes | last1=Miller | first1=M. Coleman | last2=Colbert | first2=E. J. M. | journal=International Journal of Modern Physics D | year=2004 | volume=13 | issue=1 | page=1 | doi=10.1142/S0218271804004426 | arxiv=astro-ph/0308402 <!--| s2cid=118959484-->}}</ref>研究人員假定其由一連串更小的黑洞合併形成，最終發生觀測到的合併事件。<ref name="LIGO-20200902" />

研究成員[[西北大學_(伊利諾伊州)|西北大學]]的[[瓦西莉基·卡洛耶拉|瓦西莉基·卡洛耶拉]]指，這是第一次亦是到目前為止唯一一次觀測到的中介質量黑洞，亦知道了至少一種其形成的方法。<ref name="NYT-20200903">{{cite news | language=en | last=Overbye | first=Dennis | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200902193002/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/02/science/black-hole-astronomy-physics.html | archive-date=2020-09-02 | title=These Black Holes Shouldn't Exist, but There They Are - On the far side of the universe, a collision of dark giants sheds light on an invisible process of cosmic growth. | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/02/science/black-hole-astronomy-physics.html | date=2020-09-03 | work=The New York Times | accessdate= | dead-url=no }}</ref>

2021年，加利西亞高能物理研究所（IGFAE）、葡萄牙阿威羅大學、里斯本大學高級技術學院、西班牙瓦倫西亞大學和澳洲蒙納許大學的科學團隊認為GW190521並非是兩個黑洞合併產生的重力波訊號，而是兩顆[[玻色子星|玻色子星]]合併產生的。由於玻色子星的合併過程比黑洞合併要弱很多，因此計算得出的距離也比原先估計值還要近，導致最終形成的黑洞質量增加為太陽質量的250倍。

== 可能相關的電磁活動 ==
2020年6月，天文學家報告一道閃光可能與GW190521有關係，{{link-en|茲威基瞬變設施|Zwicky Transient Facility}}（{{lang|en|ZTF}}）報告發現觸發GW190521g附近的瞬變光源，但由於在數百平方度外發生，組織仍對此不確定，若黑洞合併與此有關，會是首個黑洞合併與[[電磁輻射|電磁輻射]]有關的發現<ref name="NASA-20200625" /><ref name="PRL-20200625">{{cite journal | language=en | author=Graham, M.J. | display-authors=et al. | url=https://authors.library.caltech.edu/104019/1/PhysRevLett.124.251102.pdf | title=Candidate Electromagnetic Counterpart to the Binary Black Hole Merger Gravitational-Wave Event S190521g | journal=Physical Review Letters | year=2020 | volume=124 | issue=25 | page=251102 | doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.124.251102 | pmid=32639755 | arxiv=2006.14122 | bibcode=2020PhRvL.124y1102G | access-date= | archive-date=2020-07-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200711111646/https://authors.library.caltech.edu/104019/1/PhysRevLett.124.251102.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20200625" /><ref name="SD-20200626">{{cite news | language=en | title=Black hole collision may have exploded with light | url=https://www.spacedaily.com/reports/Black_hole_collision_may_have_exploded_with_light_999.html | date=2020-06-26 | work=ScienceDaily | accessdate= | archive-date=2020-06-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626151648/https://www.spacedaily.com/reports/Black_hole_collision_may_have_exploded_with_light_999.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。黑洞合併正常來說不會發光，研究人員認為若黑洞合併發生在穿過一條不相關但相近超大質量黑洞[[吸積盤|吸積盤]]的軌道，影響吸積盤材質和光的產生，新合併後的黑洞可能以每秒200公里的速度穿越吸積盤。<ref name="IFLS-20200625" />若這個解釋正確，閃光會在約1.6年後，當黑洞再次遇到吸積盤時，再次出現。<ref name="PRL-20200625" /><ref name="IFLS-20200625" />

研究的首席天文學家馬修·格雷厄姆（{{lang|en|Matthew Graham}}）指，超大質量黑洞在多年來已有活動，這次突然的閃光發生的時間和位置都與引力波事件吻合，研究亦認為閃光很可能與黑洞合併有關，但不能排除其他可能性。<ref name="IFLS-20200625">{{cite news | language=en | last=Carpineti | first=Alfredo | title=Astronomers May Have Observed The First Flare From A Black Hole Collision | url=https://www.iflscience.com/space/astronomers-may-have-observed-the-first-flare-from-a-black-hole-collision/ | date=2020-06-25 | work=IFLScience | accessdate= | archive-date=2020-06-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200629155728/https://www.iflscience.com/space/astronomers-may-have-observed-the-first-flare-from-a-black-hole-collision/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>

